properties.name: Big Ben
properties.description: Posted by ElizabethcolemanLondon, EnglandBig Ben is one of London\'s best-known landmarks. A light shines above the clock face when parliament is in session. The four dials of the clock are 23 feet, and the minute hand is 14 feet. The clock tower of the Palace of Westminster took 13 years to build, and is 316 feet high. The name Big Ben refers to the thirteen ton bell hung in it. The bell was named after the maker, Sir Benjamin Hall. The tower began being built after a disastrous fire which destroyed the Palace of Westminster in 1834.

properties.name: Buckingham Palace
properties.description: Posted by ElizabethcolemanLondon, EnglandBuckingham Palace is one of the major tourist attractions in London, and is one of several castles owned by the British Royal family. The original building was constructed by the duke of Buckingham, John Sheffield, as a countryhouse in 1705. King George III bought it in 1761 for his wife and had it altered by William Chambers. A part of this palace is still used today by the Royal family. A flag is hoisted each time the Queen is in the castle. Other parts of the castle can be visited. Buckingham Palace has more than 50,000 people visit the palace each year as guests to banquets, lunches, dinners, receptions and the royal garden parties.

properties.name: The Eiffel Tower
properties.description: Posted by ElizabethcolemanParis, FranceApproximately 200 million people have come to see the Eiffel Tower. The Eiffel tower was created 1887-1889 by Alexandre Gustave Eiffel in celebration of the French Revolution. The month of the completion of the Eiffel tower is March 28, 89. It took 2 years 2 months and 5 days to complete it.

properties.name: The Great Wall Of China
properties.description: Posted by ElizabethcolemanChinaThe Great Wall of China is one of the greatest wonders of the world. The Great Wall winds up and down across deserts, grasslands, mountains and plateaus, stretching approximately 6,700 kilometers from east to west of China. The Great Wall of China was built over 2,000 years ago, by Qin Shi Huangdi, the first emperor of China. The Great Wall was originally built in defense of Yan, Zhao and Qin. It is one of the largest building construction projects that was ever completed. The Great Wall can be seen from Earth orbit.

properties.name: The Leaning Tower of Pisa
properties.description: Posted by ElizabethcolemanItalyThe Tower of Pisa is the bell tower of the Cathedral. Its construction began in the August 1173 and continued (with two long interruptions) for about two hundred years, whose architect is still uncertain. The Tower was designed to be "vertical" and even if it did not lean it would still be one of the most remarkable bell towers in Europe. It started to incline during its construction. It is 187 feet high and until 1990 was leaning over at about a 10-degree angle. The top is 17 feet further over than was originally intended. The tower\'s lean increases by about one inch every 20 years.

properties.name: The London Eye
properties.description: Posted by ElizabethcolemanLondon, EnglandThe London Eye is the tallest observation wheel in the world. Since opening in March 2000, The London Eye has become an iconic landmark and a symbol of modern Britain. It carries 3.5 million customers every year. The London Eye is a unique structure, making the best of British architecture and design, rising above London\'s skyline at 135 metres. The London Eye can carry 800 passengers per revolution. The London Eye has won over 75 awards for national and international tourism, outstanding architectural quality and engineering achievement since March 2000.

properties.name: The Statue of Liberty
properties.description: Posted by ElizabethcolemanNew York CityThe Statue of Liberty, located on Ellis Island, was a gift of friendship from the people of France to the people of the United States. It is a universal symbol of freedom and democracy. The Statue of Liberty was dedicated on October 28, 1886. It was designated as a National Monument in 1924. The 25 windows in the crown symbolize gemstones found on the earth and heaven\'s rays shining over the world. The seven rays of the crown of the Statue represent the continents of the world, and the seven seas. The tablet which the Statue holds in her left hand reads "July 4th, 1776." The total weight of copper in the Statue is 62,000 pounds and the total weight of steel in the Statue is 250,000 pounds. The total weight of the Statue\'s concrete foundation is 54 million pounds.

properties.name: The Tower of London
properties.description: Posted by Elizabethcolemanlondon, englansThe Tower of London, located in London, England, was first built in 1078 by William the Conqueror. It was completed by William II who was killed by Walter Tyrell in a hunting accident in the New Forest. Over the coarse of the Towers history it has been a palace, prison, treasury, zoo and arsenal. The Tower of London is on the River Thames and is next to Tower Bridge. The Crown Jewels are also housed in the Tower of London. There are tours you can take around the towers. You can see the Crown Jewels, old art, the rooms and buildings, and more.

properties.name: The White House
properties.description: Posted by ElizabethcolemanWashington D.CThe White House, home of the president, is located in Washington D.C. It has stood as a symbol of the Presidency, the United States government, and the American people for two hundred years. It has been the executive residence of every president since John Adams. He first moved in to the building on November 1, 1800. There are 132 rooms, 35 bathrooms, and 6 levels in the Residence. The White House is 168 feet long. It was built between 1792 and 1800 of white-painted Aquia sandstone in the late Georgian style. In 1814, during the War of 1812, the White House was set on fire by British troops in the Battle of York. Only the outer walls remained, and they had to be torn down and mostly reconstructed due to weakening from the fire but was rebuilt in 1824.

properties.name: Tower Bridge(London Bridge)
properties.description: Posted by ElizabethcolemanLondon, EnglandThis bridge, the Tower/London Bridge, is located in London, England. The Tower Bridge was named after its two impressive towers, and is one of London\'s best known landmarks. It was designed by Wolfe Barry and Horace Jones, and completed in 1894. This bridge is now more than 100 years old. The bridge is 60 meters (197 ft) long and its towers rise to 43 meters. The middle of the bridge can be raised to allow large vessels to pass it.
